<title>JAPAN: Nippon Oil buys Repsol's North Sea Magnus stake.</title>
<headline>Nippon Oil buys Repsol's North Sea Magnus stake.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1996-12-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Refiner Nippon Oil Co Ltd said on Friday a subsidiary had signed a contract with Repsol SA to buy the Spanish company's five percent stake in the North Sea Magnus oil field.</p>
<p>The Magnus field produces about 100,000 barrels per day (bpd) of crude oil and 42 million cubic feet per day of natural gas, Nippon Oil said in a statement.</p>
<p>Magnus' operator is British Petroleum Co Plc, which has an 85 percent stake in the field.</p>
<p>Other shareholders are Italy's Agip SpA with five percent and Brazilian state oil firm Petrobras and Canada's Talisman Energy Inc with a 2.5 percent stake each.</p>
<p>-- Tokyo Energy Desk +81-3-5473-3708</p>
